==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sensualist
<hw>Sen"su*al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[CF. F.
<ets>sensualiste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who is sensual; one
given to the indulgence of the appetites or senses as the means of
happiness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who holds to the doctrine of
sensualism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sensualistic</ent>⟦br⟧
